{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Supplementary diagnosis from duplicate bfe1 (independently confirmed the same root cause during epic-6982 landing): the ~485873652 Mode-D recovery (_recover_from_invalid_object, read-tree HEAD + re-add current path) reduced damage ~6-8x (146->~17 lost) but does NOT cover the HEAD-REACHABLE vanished-object case — failing logs show the same object sha for the same path cascading across sequential bursts, i.e. a committed object caught by the background repack; read-tree HEAD reinstates the broken ref and the one-shot retry fails identically. Suggest the real fix also make _recover_from_invalid_object a BOUNDED LOOP that regenerates a HEAD-reachable missing object from the intact worktree file before retry, in addition to disabling background auto-maintenance under the write lock. Full write-up on bfe1."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784322177823410001,"uuid":"7cd377f5-5e14-41ba-a6b8-9a8d92522868"}